QuickNews — Privacy Policy
Effective date: 18 April 2025
Package: com.quicknews.mobile

1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how QuickNews ("we", "our", or "the App") handles information when you use our mobile application. QuickNews is a read-only news aggregation app that presents the top five global news stories, refreshed automatically via a cloud backend. We are committed to full compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and all applicable European Union privacy law.

2. Data Controller
QuickNews is operated by an independent developer based in the European Union. If you have any questions or requests regarding your personal data, please contact us via the developer contact details provided on the QuickNews page in the Google Play Store.

3. Data We Collect
3.1 Data We Do NOT Collect
QuickNews does not collect, store, or process any of the following:

Personal identifiers (name, email address, phone number)
User accounts or login credentials
Location data
Device contacts, camera, or microphone data
Financial or payment information
Browsing history or behaviour profiles

3.2 Data Processed Automatically by Third-Party Services
QuickNews uses Google Firebase (Firestore) solely to receive pre-fetched news content written by our cloud backend. When your device connects to Firebase, Google may automatically process certain technical data as part of providing the service, including:

IP address (processed by Google, not stored by us)
Device type and operating system version (processed by Google)
Timestamps of Firestore read requests (processed by Google)

This technical data is processed by Google LLC under their own Privacy Policy and Data Processing Terms. We do not have access to or control over this data.

4. Purpose and Legal Basis for Processing
The only processing activity attributable to QuickNews is delivering news content to your device via Firebase Firestore. The legal basis for this under GDPR Article 6 is:

Legitimate interests (Article 6(1)(f)): delivering the core functionality of the App requires a network connection to retrieve news content. No personal data is collected by us in this process.


5. Third-Party Services
5.1 Google Firebase (Firestore)
Used exclusively to deliver news content to the App. Firebase is operated by Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. Google processes connection metadata as a data processor under the EU Standard Contractual Clauses. For details, see https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
5.2 Perplexity AI
Our cloud backend uses Perplexity AI to research and summarise news stories. This service is called exclusively from our server-side Cloud Function and has no direct interaction with your device or personal data.
5.3 External News Sources
The App displays links to original news articles. If you choose to tap a link, you will be directed to a third-party website in your device browser. That website's own privacy policy will apply from that point.

6. Data Retention
We do not retain any personal data. Firebase Firestore retains only the news content document (news/top5), which contains no user information. Connection logs held by Google are subject to Google's own retention policies.

7. International Data Transfers
Firebase infrastructure may process connection data outside the European Economic Area. Google LLC participates in the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework and implements Standard Contractual Clauses to ensure an adequate level of protection for any such transfers.

8. Your Rights Under GDPR
As a resident of the European Union or European Economic Area you have the following rights regarding your personal data:

Right of access: to know what personal data we hold about you
Right to rectification: to correct inaccurate personal data
Right to erasure: to request deletion of your personal data
Right to restriction: to limit how we process your data
Right to data portability: to receive your data in a portable format
Right to object: to object to processing based on legitimate interests

Because QuickNews does not collect or store any personal data, most of these rights cannot be practically exercised against us directly. For rights relating to data processed by Google Firebase, please refer to Google's privacy controls at https://myaccount.google.com/privacy
You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your national data protection authority if you believe your rights have been infringed.

9. Children's Privacy
QuickNews does not knowingly collect any personal data from children under the age of 16. The App contains no features that target or are designed for use by children. If you believe a child has provided personal data through the App, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

10. Security
All communication between the App and Firebase Firestore is encrypted in transit using TLS. Firebase offline persistence is enabled on your device so that previously fetched news content can be read without an internet connection; this data is stored locally by the Firebase SDK and contains no personal information.

11. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the effective date at the top of this document and publish the updated policy at the URL listed in the Google Play Store listing. Continued use of the App after any changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

12. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or the way QuickNews handles data, please contact us via the developer contact details provided on the QuickNews page in the Google Play Store.
